From the Laravel docs on [Constraining Eager Loads](https://laravel.com/docs/6.x/eloquent-relationships#constraining-eager-loads)

&gt; [!] The `limit` and `take` query builder methods may not be used when constraining eager loads.

So you would have to create another relationship method on your class `Category` like this

```php
public function lastPosts()
{
  return $this-&gt;hasMany(&#39;App\Post&#39;)-&gt;take(4);
}
```
then use it instead

```php
$allcats = Category::whereHas(&#39;posts&#39;)-&gt;with(&#39;lastPosts&#39;)-&gt;get();
```

Or use a raw query

```php
$allcats = Category::whereHas(&#39;posts&#39;)-&gt;with([&#39;posts&#39; =&gt; function($q){
            $q-&gt;orderBy(&#39;created_at&#39;)-&gt;selectRaw(&#39;max(4)&#39;);
}])-&gt;get();
```

Hope this helps

